The paper proposes a framework for lung segmentation in chest X-rays using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The use of radiorealistic abnormalities generation for data augmentation involves image-to-image translation, which is a popular topic in the computer vision community and can be categorized under cs.AI. The paper also focuses on medical imaging, specifically chest X-rays, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.Medical Imaging. Finally, the proposed framework utilizes attention mechanisms and deep learning, which are common techniques in the deep learning (cs.DL) community.
